eatonPduMIB.name: eatonPduMIB

revisions.description: Initial Version of eatonPduMIB. Provides objects for PDU, Panel, and Breaker levels.

eatonPduMIB.contactinfo: Eaton Power Quality Technical Support (PQTS) group www.eaton.com/powerxpert Technical Resource Center phone numbers United States: 1.800.843.9433 or 919.870.3028 Canada: 1.800.461.9166 ext. 260 All other countries: Call your local service representative.
eatonPduMIB.description: The MIB module for Eaton PDUs (Power Distribution Units). Copyright (C) Eaton Corporation (2007).

PositiveInteger.name: PositiveInteger
PositiveInteger.description: This data type is a non-zero and non-negative value.

NonNegativeInteger.name: NonNegativeInteger
NonNegativeInteger.description: This data type is a non-negative value.

pduRatingVA.name: pduRatingVA
pduRatingVA.description: The full VA rating of this PDU (for all phases).

pduNominalOutputVoltage.name: pduNominalOutputVoltage
pduNominalOutputVoltage.description: The nominal Output Voltage of this PDU (as distributed to the panels). May differ from the nominal Input Voltage if the PDU has an input transformer. This is either Line-to-Line or Line-to-Neutral, as indicated in pduOutputVoltageUnits.

pduNumPhases.name: pduNumPhases
pduNumPhases.description: The number of lines (phases) for this PDU. The number of Input phases must equal the number of Output phases.

pduNumPanels.name: pduNumPanels
pduNumPanels.description: The number of panels or subfeeds contained in this PDU system. This determines the number of rows found in the panel tables.

pduFrequency.name: pduFrequency
pduFrequency.description: The present frequency reading for the full PDU.

pduInputVA.name: pduInputVA
pduInputVA.description: The present VA input demand of the full PDU system.

pduInputPower.name: pduInputPower
pduInputPower.description: The present input power demand of the full PDU system.

pduInputPowerFactor.name: pduInputPowerFactor
pduInputPowerFactor.description: The input power factor for the full PDU system. Varies from -1.00 to 1.00, multiplied by 100. If negative values are used, they indicate lagging pf.

pduGroundCurrent.name: pduGroundCurrent
pduGroundCurrent.description: The present current in the PDU's ground phase. Ideally, this value stays at 0.

pduInputVoltageUnits.name: pduInputVoltageUnits
pduInputVoltageUnits.description: Indicates whether the pduInputPhaseVoltage readings are 'Vrms Line-Line' or 'Vrms Line-Neutral'.

pduInputNumPhases.name: pduInputNumPhases
pduInputNumPhases.description: The number of input phases for this PDU. This variable indicates the number of rows in the pduInputTable.

pduInputTable.name: pduInputTable
pduInputTable.description: A list of input table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of pduInputNumPhases.

pduInputEntry.name: pduInputEntry
pduInputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input phase.

pduInputPhaseVoltage.name: pduInputPhaseVoltage
pduInputPhaseVoltage.description: The present input voltage for this phase.

pduInputPhaseCurrent.name: pduInputPhaseCurrent
pduInputPhaseCurrent.description: The present input current for this phase.

pduInputPhasePercentLoad.name: pduInputPhasePercentLoad
pduInputPhasePercentLoad.description: The percentage of the pdu power capacity presently being used on this line, normally based on the ratio of pduInputPhaseCurrent to the rated input current.

pduOutputKilowattHours.name: pduOutputKilowattHours
pduOutputKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hour value for the full PDU system since the last reset.

pduOutputVA.name: pduOutputVA
pduOutputVA.description: The present VA output of the full PDU system.

pduOutputPower.name: pduOutputPower
pduOutputPower.description: The present output power of the full PDU system.

pduOutputPowerFactor.name: pduOutputPowerFactor
pduOutputPowerFactor.description: The output power factor for the full PDU system. Varies from -1.00 to 1.00, multiplied by 100. If negative values are used, they indicate lagging pf.

pduNeutralCurrent.name: pduNeutralCurrent
pduNeutralCurrent.description: The present current in the PDU's output neutral phase. Ideally, this value stays at 0.

pduRatedOutputCurrent.name: pduRatedOutputCurrent
pduRatedOutputCurrent.description: The rated current value for one PDU Output phase at full load (100%).

pduOutputVoltageUnits.name: pduOutputVoltageUnits
pduOutputVoltageUnits.description: Indicates whether the pduOutputPhaseVoltage readings are 'Vrms Line-Line' or 'Vrms Line-Neutral'.

pduOutputNumPhases.name: pduOutputNumPhases
pduOutputNumPhases.description: The number of output phases for this PDU. This variable indicates the number of rows in the pduOutputTable.

pduOutputTable.name: pduOutputTable
pduOutputTable.description: A list of output table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of pduOutputNumPhases.

pduOutputEntry.name: pduOutputEntry
pduOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output phase.

pduOutputPhaseVoltage.name: pduOutputPhaseVoltage
pduOutputPhaseVoltage.description: The present output voltage for this phase.

pduOutputPhaseCurrent.name: pduOutputPhaseCurrent
pduOutputPhaseCurrent.description: The present output current for this phase.

pduOutputPhasePercentLoad.name: pduOutputPhasePercentLoad
pduOutputPhasePercentLoad.description: The percentage of the pdu power capacity presently being used on this line, normally based on the ratio of pduOutputPhaseCurrent to pduRatedOutputCurrent.

panelRatingsTable.name: panelRatingsTable
panelRatingsTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially numbered) table of ratings for each panel. The number of entries is given by the value of pduNumPanels.

panelRatingsEntry.name: panelRatingsEntry
panelRatingsEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output phase.

panelNumber.name: panelNumber
panelNumber.description: Index for the Panel Ratings and Meters tables. Corresponds to the physical panel number in the PDU system. There must be a #1. The maximum value is 16. Panels are not required to be numbered sequentially.

panelRatedVoltage.name: panelRatedVoltage
panelRatedVoltage.description: The nominal Voltage of this panel (as distributed to the breakers or subfeeds). This is either Line-to-Line or Line-to-Neutral, as indicated in panelVoltageUnits.

panelRatedBreakerCurrent.name: panelRatedBreakerCurrent
panelRatedBreakerCurrent.description: The rated current value for one panel (input) phase at full load (100%). This is set by the panel's input breaker; if there is no input breaker for this panel, then this object is not accessible.

panelNumPhases.name: panelNumPhases
panelNumPhases.description: The number of lines (phases) for this panel.

panelNumBreakers.name: panelNumBreakers
panelNumBreakers.description: The number of breakers contained in this panel. This determines the number of rows found in the breaker tables.

panelVoltageUnits.name: panelVoltageUnits
panelVoltageUnits.description: Indicates whether the panelPhaseVoltage readings are 'Vrms Line-Line' or 'Vrms Line-Neutral'.

panelMetersTable.name: panelMetersTable
panelMetersTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially numbered) table of ratings for each panel. The number of entries is given by the value of pduNumPanels.

panelMetersEntry.name: panelMetersEntry
panelMetersEntry.description: An entry containing meter readings applicable to a particular panel.

panelTotalKilowattHours.name: panelTotalKilowattHours
panelTotalKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this panel since it was commissioned and put into service, or since the last reset of the system KHW measures.

panelMonthlyKilowattHours.name: panelMonthlyKilowattHours
panelMonthlyKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this panel since the beginning of this calendar month, or since the last reset of the system KHW measures.

panelYtdKilowattHours.name: panelYtdKilowattHours
panelYtdKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this panel since the beginning of this calendar year (YTD), or since the last reset of the system KHW measures.

panelVA.name: panelVA
panelVA.description: The present VA (input) demand of this panel.

panelPower.name: panelPower
panelPower.description: The present power (input) demand of this panel.

panelPowerFactor.name: panelPowerFactor
panelPowerFactor.description: The input power factor for this panel. Varies from -1.00 to 1.00, multiplied by 100. If negative values are used, they indicate lagging pf.

panelNeutralCurrent.name: panelNeutralCurrent
panelNeutralCurrent.description: The present neutral phase current for this panel.

panelPhaseMetersTable.name: panelPhaseMetersTable
panelPhaseMetersTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially panel numbered) table of ratings for each panel. The number of entries is given by the sum of panelNumPhases for pduNumPanels.

panelPhaseMetersEntry.name: panelPhaseMetersEntry
panelPhaseMetersEntry.description: An entry containing meter readings applicable to a particular phase of a particular panel.

panelPhaseVoltage.name: panelPhaseVoltage
panelPhaseVoltage.description: The present voltage for this phase.

panelPhaseCurrent.name: panelPhaseCurrent
panelPhaseCurrent.description: The present current for this phase.

panelPhasePercentLoad.name: panelPhasePercentLoad
panelPhasePercentLoad.description: The percentage of the panel power capacity presently being used on this line, normally based on the ratio of panelPhaseCurrent to the rated phase current.

breakerRatingsTable.name: breakerRatingsTable
breakerRatingsTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially numbered) table of ratings and fixed values for each breaker. The number of entries is given by the value of panelNumBreakers for this panel.

breakerRatingsEntry.name: breakerRatingsEntry
breakerRatingsEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output phase.

breakerNumber.name: breakerNumber
breakerNumber.description: Index for the Breaker Ratings and Meters tables. Corresponds to the physical breaker number in the PDU system. Breakers are not required to be numbered sequentially.

breakerName.name: breakerName
breakerName.description: Name given by the administrator to identify this breaker.

breakerRatedCurrent.name: breakerRatedCurrent
breakerRatedCurrent.description: The rated current value of this breaker (for one phase) at full load (100%).

breakerNumPhases.name: breakerNumPhases
breakerNumPhases.description: The number of lines (phases) for this breaker.

breakerMetersTable.name: breakerMetersTable
breakerMetersTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially numbered) table of ratings for each breaker. The number of entries is given by the value of panelNumBreakers for this panel.

breakerMetersEntry.name: breakerMetersEntry
breakerMetersEntry.description: An entry containing meter readings applicable to a particular breaker.

breakerTotalKilowattHours.name: breakerTotalKilowattHours
breakerTotalKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this breaker since it was commissioned and put into service, or since the last reset of the panel KHW measures.

breakerMonthlyKilowattHours.name: breakerMonthlyKilowattHours
breakerMonthlyKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this breaker since the beginning of this calendar month, or since the last reset of the panel KHW measures.

breakerYtdKilowattHours.name: breakerYtdKilowattHours
breakerYtdKilowattHours.description: The accumulated kilowatt-hours for this breaker since the beginning of this calendar year (YTD), or since the last reset of the panel KHW measures.

breakerPhaseMetersTable.name: breakerPhaseMetersTable
breakerPhaseMetersTable.description: A sparsely populated (ie, not sequentially breaker numbered) table of ratings for each breaker. The number of entries is given by the sum of breakerNumPhases for panelNumBreakers for all panels (pduNumPanels).

breakerPhaseMetersEntry.name: breakerPhaseMetersEntry
breakerPhaseMetersEntry.description: An entry containing meter readings applicable to a particular phase of a particular breaker on a particular panel.

breakerPhaseVA.name: breakerPhaseVA
breakerPhaseVA.description: The present VA (input) demand of this phase on this breaker.

breakerPhasePower.name: breakerPhasePower
breakerPhasePower.description: The present power (input) demand of phase on this breaker.

breakerPhasePowerFactor.name: breakerPhasePowerFactor
breakerPhasePowerFactor.description: The input power factor for this phase on this breaker. Varies from -1.00 to 1.00, multiplied by 100. If negative values are used, they indicate lagging pf.

breakerPhaseCurrent.name: breakerPhaseCurrent
breakerPhaseCurrent.description: The present current for this phase of this breaker.

breakerPhasePercentLoad.name: breakerPhasePercentLoad
breakerPhasePercentLoad.description: The percentage of the breaker power capacity presently being used on this line, normally based on the ratio of breakerPhaseCurrent to the breakerRatedCurrent.

pdu3phaseCompliance.name: pdu3phaseCompliance
pdu3phaseCompliance.description: The compliance statement for a normal 3-phase PDU, which implements the full set of objects.
